summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed, executed on the 24th day of June, A. D., 1896, by Andrew F. Burleigh, Receiver of the Northern Pacific Railroad Company, and the Central Trust Company of New York, Trustee, by G. Shermen, its Vice President, to the City of Seattle, for the S. W. 1/4 of the S. W. 1/4, of Section 23, Township 22 North, Range 6 East of the W. M., containing 40 acres, more or less.
